From sarora at fhcrc.org  Thu Jun  5 02:27:29 2014
From: sarora at fhcrc.org (Sonali Arora)
Date: Wed, 04 Jun 2014 17:27:29 -0700
Subject: [Bioc-devel] recommend biocViews
Message-ID: <538FB971.1030604@fhcrc.org>

Hi Everyone,

We have come up with a new function called "recommendBiocViews" which will
recommend biocViews to package Contributors by parsing the DESCRIPTION 
file,
man page and  vignettes of their package.

We also ran this function on all the "Software" packages in Rpacks(devel 
branch)
to recommend additional biocViews for existing packages.

You can find the results in the attached file.

A small demo using the package "RefNet"

 > data <- read.delim("recommendbiocViews.txt", row.names=1)
 > data["RefNet",]

current                  recommended remove
RefNet GraphAndNetwork ThirdPartyClient, DataImport

It returns 4 columns:
column1 - current - existing biocViews which are present in ReferNet's
DESCRIPTION file

column2 - recommended - recommended biocViews which you can add in 
addition to
existing biocViews (This is a recommended list - Please go through this 
list and
find which biocViews best describe your package)

column3 - remove - existing biocViews which are inconsistent with current
Bioconductor biocViews
( Hint - you have a biocView which is discontinued, its spelling has 
changed
( pay attention to cases, plural etc) )

Please remember that adding terms which are not part of the Bioconductor
biocViews will not lead to any additional visibility of your package.

Also misspelled biocViews in your package will lead to 'no-show' of your
package on the biocViews page.
eg: If you have 'CopyNumberVariations' in your DESCRIPTION file - your
package will not show up under 'CopyNumberVariation'

For a new package that you're developing, Please use BiocViews(Version: 
1.33.4)
 > library(BiocViews)
 > recommendedBiocViews("packageDirectory")

A similar 3 column list is returned by parsing your package.

If you feel that these biocViews are appropriately recommended for your 
package,
Please add them to your package.

-- 
Thanks and Regards,
Sonali.

